{
  "text": "Now, we create public subnets. The word public means these subnets' exetnets of 9, East of 1DS and East of 1B. This provides redundancy. If one zone fails, your infrastructure keeps running. Each subnet gets a slash 24 CIDR block, which is 256 IP addresses. Notice the map publicative and launch flag is set to true. This automatically assigns public IT addresses true. This is required for internet access to not 0.0.0.0.0.0.0.0.",
